meaning_str.bing:
adj. 意想不到的；令人惊奇的；奇怪的；不平常的
网络. 特别的；非凡的；非常的

意想不到的；令人惊奇的；奇怪的；不平常的

非凡的；卓越的；杰出的；令人惊奇的；异常的；异乎寻常的；不同寻常的；特别的；特殊的
（公司正常业务活动之外的）特别项目；特殊账目；非常账目；特别费用；额外开支

1.en: His famous book, The Travels of Marco Polo, indicates that he was a man of extraordinary bravery, brilliance, and strength.
1.cn: 他的名著的马可波罗游记，表明他是一个非凡的勇敢，辉煌的人，和力量。

2.en: That's how the Catholic Church was built, tremendous treasures there, extraordinary valuable jewels and all that.
2.cn: 天主教廷就是那么建造的，那里有不计其数的财富，价值连城的珠宝，等待。

3.en: Obviously, it's an extraordinary personal moment, but, you know, you don't have to go back to slavery.
3.cn: 很明显，这是一个非凡的个人时刻，但你知道，你不必回答奴隶制。

0.cn: 索尔和本德确实是非凡的数学家。

1.en: But I want to encourage every one of you who has supported me to join me in supporting this extraordinary woman, the First Lady of the United States, Claire Hale Underwood.
1.cn: 但我想让支持我的各位和我一起支持这位非凡的女性，美国第一夫人，克莱尔·黑尔·安德伍德。

2.en: We live at an extraordinary time in the life of the universe where we can start to understand the universe's journey and view a history that plays itself out on the sky for all of us to see.
2.cn: 我们生活在一个对于宇宙生命来讲意义非凡的时代，在在这样的时代我们能够去了解宇宙的历程，同时也能够去了解它那呈现在天空中为我们每个人所展示的历史。

4.en: Ladies and gentlemen, what an extraordinary moment this is.
4.cn: 各位女士，各位先生，这真是不平凡的一刻。

5.en: This is TV on a huge scale. And it is extraordinary.
5.cn: 这个电视台规模庞大。绝对让你叹为观止。

6.en: You are extraordinary, my sons, unlike anything the world has ever seen.
6.cn: 孩子们，你们是非比寻常的，是世间绝无仅有的。

7.en: You want extraordinary measures or should I just unplug you? Use your judgment.
7.cn: 你想要不同寻常的治疗方法，还是拔管后自生自灭？你来判断。

8.en: Like Greg, Robert inherited a family business which has seen extraordinary change.
8.cn: 和格雷格一样,罗伯特也继承了家族产业，也经历了明显的变化。

9.en: Together we'll do extraordinary things. Just give me the Stone! You liar! Kill him!
9.cn: 你我合作，可以干出一番惊天动地的事来，快把魔法石给我。你这骗子。杀了他。

10.en: Individuals with extraordinary abilities may already be among us. Thank you very much.
10.cn: 具有非凡能力的个人 可能已经在我们中间。非常感谢。

11.en: This was mine. How extraordinary! And it looks the same as it did the last time I saw it.
11.cn: 这是我的，真不可思议跟我最后一次看到它时一模一样。

12.en: These stones, it seems, can only be brandished by beings of extraordinary strength. Observe.
12.cn: 这些宝石，只有具超强力量的个体才能驾驭，请看。

13.en: Actually, there is one more thing. Anna, you are the most extraordinary person I've ever known.
13.cn: 其实，还有一件事，安娜，你是我见过最了不起的人。

14.en: Last night, I experienced something new, an extraordinary meal from a singularly unexpected source.
14.cn: 昨晚我有个全新的体验，一顿奇妙的菜肴来自令人意想不到的出处!

15.en: And no one sacrifices more to preserve our blessings than our extraordinary men and women in uniform.
15.cn: 没有谁比我们优秀的男女军人牺牲了更多来保护我们的福祉。

16.en: You know that while you are extraordinary on your own, we are all stronger and can be louder together.
16.cn: 你们知道，虽然你们每个人都很出色，但团结起来后 你们将会更强 并能发出更大的声音。

17.en: How is it that a baby with no extraordinary magical talent was able to defeat the greatest wizard of all time?
17.cn: 我不懂为什么一个没什么魔法天赋的婴儿竟然可以打败有史以来最伟大的巫师？

18.en: Monet! You know his work? Of course. Look at his use of color here. Isn't he great? I know. It's extraordinary.
18.cn: 莫内的画。你知道他的作品? 当然，你看他用色，真棒。对啊，好棒。

19.en: But Ted doesn't just grow tomatoes. Like his neighbors, he produces an extraordinary variety of different crops.
19.cn: 但泰德种的不止是番茄，和他的邻居一样，他种了许许多多各种各样的作物。
